      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE PARKED NZ (2) has had wide or second row draws in each of his three starts since switching from NZ and all of those efforts have had merit. Race fit now and a much more favourable barrier gives him the chance to show what he can do. RUMBLE STRIP NZ (4) is progressing nicely, winning his last three outings at this circuit and distance. This is stronger but each of those wins was from a wider or second row draw and he has upside. ULTIMATE MIKI (3) comes off his first defeat in WA but he drew on the back row and worked so was far from disgraced in fifth. Won three in a row at this circuit and distance prior and should get his chance from the low draw. LAST HARD COPY (7) was a winner at this circuit and distance back in April and is working towards another having come from the second line when runner-up last week. BELLY UP (8) deserves respect having come from this barrier to win here three back.",
